**Currency**:
The official currency is the Communauté financière africaine [franc](/Franc) ([CFAF](/CFAF)), which is subdivided into 100 [centimes](/Centime).

**Exchange Rates**:
The CFAF has experienced fluctuations against the US dollar over the years, with rates such as 507.71 CFAF per US$1 in 2010, 472.19 in 2009, and 447.81 in 2008. A significant policy shift occurred on January 1, 1999, when the CFAF was pegged to the [euro](/Euro) at a fixed rate of 655.957 CFA francs per euro.

